On the other hand, how dinosaurs managed to become the dominant tetrapodes of the secondary era as they proved a relatively rare collateral line of the reptile branch, still remains a mystery.
At the time of the Trias, the dinosaurs shared their habitat with many other reptiles, such as with the ancestors of current crocodiles and with many other Saurians.
